3.13 Plain data structures
Plain Clojure data structures have recursive kind semantics: * Each tool has its own way to represent them visually (e.g., Clay just uses text, while Portal has a hierarchical navigation UI).

(list 1 "A" :B 'C)


(1 "A" :B C)


[1 "A" :B 'C]


[1 "A" :B C]


#{1 "A" :B 'C}


#{1 :B C "A"}


{1 "A" :B 'C}


{1 "A", :B C}
